# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Contact Form → Telegram (via Supabase Edge Function)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All contact form submissions are routed through the Supabase
# Edge Function "contact-form" so the bot token is never exposed
# in the client bundle.
#
# Set these as Edge Function secrets in the Supabase dashboard:
#   Dashboard → Edge Functions → contact-form → Secrets
#
# Required:
#   TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN   – get from @BotFather on Telegram
#
# Contact submissions are hard-routed to Telegram ID `905513579` in code.
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_IDS / TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID / TELEGRAM_FALLBACK_CHAT_ID are not used.
#   CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS – comma-separated allowed origins (empty = wildcard)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase (client-side — only needed for admin features)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Direct Telegram API Fallback (client-side, optional)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When set, these allow the contact form to send messages
# directly to Telegram as a last-resort fallback if the
# Supabase Edge Function is unreachable.
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY: These values will be embedded in the client JS
#    bundle and visible to anyone. Only enable if you accept
#    this tradeoff (e.g. bot has minimal permissions, group is
#    non-sensitive).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABC-DEF...
# VITE_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID is ignored (recipient is fixed to 905513579 in code)
